         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">30/7/90 ¶  ¶ Herewith, dear Professor, I return to you the unique specimen of the last sending. It seems to be a form of B. ¶  ¶ diacantha, ¶ Bassia dicantha? ¶  ¶ of which the genuine Sclerolaena uni...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">90.07.30a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Ralph Tate</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Barr Smith Library, University of Adelaide, South Australia.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">30/7/90</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Herewith, dear Professor, I return to you the unique specimen of the last sending. It seems to be a form of B.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>diacantha,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Bassia dicantha</seg>?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of which the genuine Sclerolaena uniflora is a short-thorned variety.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The other plant, now Bassia Tatei, has opposite, broader leaves and an unilaterally bulging fruit. It is now drawn and can still be included in that decade of the Salsolaceae, which comprises Bassia.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to R. Tate, 18 July<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1890 (in this edition as 90-07-18b),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to R. Tate, 24 July 1890. The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>figure<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Bassia tatei</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>appeared in B91.13.24,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Decade 8,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>plate LXXI.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If some weeks hence, when I hope to be freer for botanic work, you can send me kindly a few more specimens of your Caladenia toxochila, C. tentaculata, and of Fitzgerald's C. reticulata &amp; C. leptochila<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Described in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Tate (1889b) and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>R.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Fitzgerald (1882).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">(should you have specimens to spare), I would like to study them in connection with my large material also from W.A. here.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When you get later leisure, kindly say, which of Mr Tietken's species should be recorded as additional for the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">W.A</hi>
               </seg>. territory in the Census.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>You are clearer on this subject than I am.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to R. Tate, 1 July 1890<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 90-07-01a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Bassia diacantha</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Bassia Tatei</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Caladenia leptochila</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Caladenia reticulata</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Caladenia tentaculata</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Caladenia toxochila</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Salsolaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sclerolaena uniflora</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
